<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1303689>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Structures of Ambrysus buenoi. (A) dorsal habitus of male, (B) 6th and 7th abdominal terga of male, (C) 8th abdominal tergum of male, (D) ventral surface of phallosoma, (E) left side of phallososma, (F) sternum VI and subgenital plate of female (terminal abdominal segments removed; arrow indicates posterior margin of laterosternite VI). agp = accessory genitalic process, al = apical lobe, ldf = left dorsal flap, lvl = left ventral lobe, mc = medial convexity, plc = posterolateral corner, pp = pseudoparamere, sct = scutellum, sgp = subgenital plate. Size bar = 0.5 mm and applies only to figures D and E." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1303689/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1303695>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Structures of Ambrysus pulchellus. (A) dorsal habitus of female, (B) 6th and 7th abdominal terga of male, (C) 8th abdominal tergum of male, (D) ventral surface of phallosoma, (E) left side of phallososma, (F) sternum VI and subgenital plate of female (terminal abdominal segments removed). plc = posterolateral corner. Size bar = 0.5 mm and applies only to figures D and E." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1303695/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

